# Copy to ftp.env (gitignored) for local reference only — CI uses GitHub Actions secrets.
#
# In GitHub: Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions → New repository secret
#
# FTP_SERVER       = Host from Namecheap (often ftp.yourdomain.com or server hostname from cPanel)
# FTP_USERNAME     = Full FTP username from Namecheap (may include @domain.com)
# FTP_PASSWORD     = FTP account password
#
# The workflow uploads into this account’s FTP root (no remote subpath in CI). In cPanel, create or
# assign the FTP user so its home directory is the folder that serves /bootcamp (e.g. public_html/bootcamp).
#
# If FTPS fails in CI, edit .github/workflows/deploy-ftp.yml and try protocol: ftp or ftps-legacy.

FTP_SERVER=ftp.example.com
FTP_USERNAME=your_ftp_user
FTP_PASSWORD=your_ftp_password